{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀσφαλ-ής</b>, ές, <br /> (σφάλλομαι, σφαλῆναι) <b>not liable to fall, immovable, steadfast,</b> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus only once as \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<i>adjective</i> (compare infr. III), θεῶν ἕδος ἀ. αἰεί[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 6.42, compare 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 128, 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 6.3, 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 2.34, etc.; ἀσφαλῆ θεῶν νόμιμα 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 454\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>unshaken,</b> of purpose, ἀ. ὁ νοῦς[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “fragment” 351. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> of friends and the like, <b>unfailing, trusty,</b> οὐ γὰρ οἱ.. εὐρύνωτοι φῶτες ἀσφαλέστατοι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Aj.” 1251; ἀ. στρατηλάτης 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 599, compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.69: with \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>infinitive</i>, φρονεῖν γὰρ οἱ ταχεῖς οὐκ ἀσφαλεῖς the hasty in counsel are not <b>safe,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 617, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Sophista” 231a; σῴζειν τὰ κοινὰ πράγματ᾽ ἀσφαλέσταται 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 1062 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of things, <b>sure, certain,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.108,etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>assured from danger, safe,</b> ἀ. αἰών[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 3.86; ἀσφαλεῖ σὺν ἐξόδῳ 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1288; ἀ. ὄρος 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Respublica Lacedaemoniorum” 12.1; ὁδός -εστέρα [prev. author] “HG” 5.4.51\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν τῷ ἀσφαλεῖ in <b>safety,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.137, 8.39, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 892e; ἐν ἀσφαλεῖ τοῦ μὴ παθεῖν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 3.3.31; τοῦ λαλεῖν 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Σαμία” 25\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν -εστέρῳ, -εστάτῳ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 7.1.21, “An.” 1.8.22; ἐν ἀ. βίου 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 785; μένειν ἐν τῷ ἀ. 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 4.7.8\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐξ ἀσφαλοῦς from <b>a place of safety,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Eq.Mag.” 4.16; τοῦ ἀσφαλέος εἵνεκα 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.109\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ ἀ., ={ἀσφάλεια}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.55, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μετὰ τοῦ αὑτῆς ἀ. with <b>no risk to</b> herself, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Plotinus Philosophus 4.8.7\">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]; ἀσφαλές [ἐστι], with <i>infinitive</i>, <b>it is safe</b> to.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.75, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 891, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 1489: _absolutely_, ἀλλ᾽ οὐκ ἀσφαλές 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Philebus” 61d, etc.; φεύγειν αὐτοῖς ἀσφαλέστερόν ἐστιν ἢ ἡμῖν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 3.2.19. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> ἀ. ῥήτωρ a <b>convincing</b> speaker, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Mem.” 4.6.15. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> in Lit. Crit., <b>sound, not risky,</b> of language or rhythm, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demetrius Phalereus Rhetor “Demetrius on Style” 19, 41. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<i>adverb</i> -ῶς, ἐρεῖ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 78. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>substantive</i> ἀσφαλές, τό, ={ἀσφάλεια}[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6, “BGU” 984.14 (4th c.AD), etc. \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <i>Epic dialect</i> <i>adverb</i> ἀσφαλέως, ἔχειν, μένειν, to be, remain <b>firm, steady,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 23.325, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 17.235: _neuter_ ἀσφαλές\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] as <i>adverb</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” (see. below); δρακεῖσ᾽ ἀσφαλές 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 2.20; ἀ. ἀγορεύει \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<b>without faltering,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.171, 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 86; ἔμπεδον ἀσφαλέως 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 13.141, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 13.86; ἔμπεδον ἀσφαλὲς αἰεί 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.683. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<i>adverb</i> ἀσφαλῶς (-έως) is used in all senses of the <i>adjective</i>, -έως βεβηκὼς ποσσί[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th c.BC: Archilochus Lyricus 58.4\">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]; <b>in safety, with certainty,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 613; ἀ. βουλεύειν 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 3.34; ἀ. ἔχει 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.86\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>infinitive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 27.6; ἀ. προσθεῖναι \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>as a precaution,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Alexander Aphrodisiensis Philosophus “in Aristotelis Meteorologicorum libros commentaria - pars” 14.10\">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]: <i>comparative</i> <b>-έστερον</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.161, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 85d;\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] but <b>-εστέρως</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “προρρητικόν” 2.15, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.71\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>superlative</i> <b>-έστατα</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “προρρητικόν” 2.23, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 467e.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0804","accentedUnicode":"ἀσφαλής","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0803","matchingForm":"ἀσφάλεια","stepTransliteration":"asfaleia","gloss":"security","_zh_tw_Gloss":"確實, 妥當","_es_Gloss":"seguridad","_zh_Gloss":"确实, 妥当"},{"strongNumber":"G0805","matchingForm":"ἀσφαλίζω","stepTransliteration":"asfalizō","gloss":"to secure","_zh_tw_Gloss":"把守妥當","_es_Gloss":"asegurar","_zh_Gloss":"把守妥当"},{"strongNumber":"G0806","matchingForm":"ἀσφαλῶς","stepTransliteration":"asfalōs","gloss":"securely","_zh_tw_Gloss":"牢牢靠靠, 嚴緊","_es_Gloss":"con seguridad","_zh_Gloss":"牢牢靠靠, 严紧"}],"shortDef":"safe, firm, certain; definite; the truth","mediumDef":"safe, firm, certain; definite; the truth <br /><i>primarily</i> <b>firm, secure from falling; firm, sure, steady, immovable,</b> <ref='Heb.6.19'>Heb. 6:19;</ref> <i>metaphorically</i> <b>certain, sure, definite</b> <ref='Act.21.34'>Acts 21:34;</ref> 22:30; 25:26; <b>safe, making secure,</b> <ref='Php.3.1'>Phil. 3:1</ref>*","stepGloss":"secure","stepTransliteration":"asfalēs","count":5,"_es_Definition":"seguro ; seguridad, digno de confianza (FIL.3:1); definido (HCH.25:26) ; los hechos o la razón (HCH.21:34; 22:30)","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 堅穩的 (來 6:19)<br>2) 肯定的, 確實的<br>3) 安全, 穩當的 (腓 3:1)","_zh_Definition":"1) 坚稳的 (来 6:19)<br>2) 肯定的, 确实的<br>3) 安全, 稳当的 (腓 3:1)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"chắc chắn, an toàn","_zh_tw_Gloss":"實情","_es_Gloss":"seguro","_zh_Gloss":"实情"}]}